              <tr><td colspan="3">  <table width="600" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr><td width="200" valign="top"><b>Imbued Northman Ring Helm (Tr)</b><br>
AC: 10<br>
+1 STR, +2 WIS, +2 CR<br>
WT: 5.5<br>
Class: WAR, BRD, ROG, SHM<br>
Race: HUM, BAR, HEF</td>

  <td width="100" align="center" valign="top">
  <b>Item Icon</b><br>
  <img src="itemicons/head003.jpg"></td>

  <td width="160" valign="top">
  <b>Obtained From</b><br>¤ Smithing Skill (0)<br>
</td>
  <td width="140" valign="top">
  <b>Additional Info</b><br>
  Type: Armor, Head<br>
AC Per Stone: 1.82<br>
Date Added: 11/08/00<br>
Last Updated: 11/15/00<br>
<img src="images/pp.gif" width="17" height="17" align="left"> <a href="JavaScript:popPrice(2962)">Price Details</a><br clear=left>
<img src="images/print_w.gif" width="17" height="17" align="left"> <a href="itemsheet.php3?id=2962" target="_blank">Printable Version</a></td></tr>
  </table>
  <br><br>
  <b>Description</b><br>
This item is created through use of the smithing skill.  Only barbarians may craft this item and it must be forged in the Northman Forge located outside McPherson's Bloody Blades in Halas.  If you try it on a normal forge, or if any other race attempts to create it, you unfortunately will fail.  Combine the following items in the Northman Forge to create the Imbued Northman Ring Helm.  This item will become trivial to smith at skill >179.
<br><br>
<li> Smithy Hammer
<li> Frost Temper
<li> Large Chain Coif Pattern
<li> Large Leather Helm
<li> Imbued Ivory [Tribunal]
<li> Medium Quality Rings x2
<br><br>
To create the Frost Temper, it requires you to use the Brewing Skill.  You must combine Brandy, Ice Goblin Blood and two Essences of Winter in a Brew Barrel.  The ice goblin blood is dropped by Ice Goblins which can be found in Permafrost and Everfrost.  For the Essence of Winter, you will need to kill Ice Giants which can be found at the entrance to Permafrost, or deep within it's depths near Lady Vox.  This item will become trivial to brew at skill 135.
<br><br>
The smithy hammer, large leather armor and the large chain patterns all can be purchased in Halas.  The medium quality rings are created by combining a Flask of Water, a Large Brick of Ore and a File, in the forge.  The imbued ivory is created through use of the imbue ivory spell.  You will need to recruit the services of a fellow shaman who can cast the spell, and one Ivory, which can be purchased from various gem merchants.  This item can only be equipped by those that worship The Tribunal.</td></tr>
